==English==
=== Adverb ===
# in a [[clear]] manner; without a [[doubt]]


==== Further common uses of the word [[clearly]] ====

[[Clearly]] has become a buzzword to create the illusion of conveying a fact, while lacking resources to back up a statement. When questioned about such facts, the person making a claim will likely resort to a distracting babble in an attempt to cover up the lack of plausible, reliable information.

Complete speculation; assumption; relayed hearsay; bias of opinion. Overconfidence of a statement having insufficient substance. Calculated risk of fact within a statement.

Use and example: I [[clearly]] understand how to write a [[wiktionary]] article. Creditability is falsely enhanced, when received by an unaware individual.

Noteworthy offenders are commonly lawyers, politicians, executives, and media spokespeople.


Cited example:

http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/businesstechnology/2003216032_msftpatent22.html

"Obviously, we're disappointed," Microsoft spokesman Jack Evans said in an e-mail. "We believe that the facts in this case [[clearly]] show that Microsoft and others developed their own product activation technologies well before z4 Technologies claims to have created this technology."


